contents:
Per. Curiam,
There appears to be no error in this case that requires correction. The questions involved—so far as they are material, or require discussion—are substantially the same as those presented and disposed of in Kennedy v. Agricultural Insurance Company, No. 69 of this term [165 Pa. 179],
For reasons given in opinion just filed in that case, neither of the assignments of error in this is sustained.
Judgment affirmed.
